
  Architectural Lesson

  This follows the SKUEL philosophy: "Type errors as teachers, showing us where components don't flow together properly."

  The MyPy error revealed that our type annotations were too vague (type), preventing the type checker from understanding that enum classes are iterable. By using the more specific type[Enum] constraint, we:

  1. Communicate intent - The parameter must be an enum class, not just any type
  2. Enable verification - MyPy can now verify iteration operations are valid
  3. Improve discoverability - IDE autocomplete works better with specific type constraints

